Here's my second map.  I took a very different direction with this one compared to the first, at least aesthetically.  However, you'll find the surf is quite fun.  This map was created with "surf for the sake of surf" in mind, so you won't find a jail or anything encouraging combat.

Type: Linear
Time: ~1:40
Filesize: 52MB (unzipped) 14MB (zipped)
Style: I'm told this is like 2005 surf, I'll let you decide.

Final note: I apologize for that water bug in the credits room, I couldn't figure out how to get rid of it.

The Surf_Water-Run Banjo Map Pack!

Thanks for taking a look at my Map Pack, here are the three maps contained in the download:

surf_water-run_banjo: The classic water-run map. Spawn with scouts, die when you fall, etc.

surf_water-run_banjo_jail: Self Explanitory. Perfect for DM or RPG Servers.

surf_water-run_banjo_skill: Spawn with no weapons, two extra stages added into the mix.

Stage 1: Secret Kool Aid Stage (Located in both surf_water-run_banjo & surf_water-run_banjo_jail)

Stage 2: Water-Run Level #1

Stage 3: Water-Run Level #2

Stage 4: Water-Run Level #3

Stage 5: Bonus stage I made. Its tough!

Secret Kool Aid Area INFO:

Theres a picture of me wearing a Kool Aid T-Shirt on Level 2 of surf_water-run_banjo and surf_water-run_banjo_jail. To access the secret Kool Aid Level you must press two buttons with the kool aid face that are located before my picture on Level 2. After pressing the second button, you have 12 seconds to reach my picture before the glass reappears.

A tier 3 surf map with 8 stages and 2 bonuses. ------------------

I have been working on this map for the past several months, and it's finally ready for release.


The Specs

  • Easy Tier 3
  • 8 Stages
  • 2 Bonuses

The mappers (by stage)

  1. FalseLogic
  2. Krazy
  3. FalseLogic
  4. Falc
  5. FalseLogic
  6. FalseLogic
  7. Juxtapo
  8. Malt

Bonus Stages:

  1. Juxtapo
  2. Furchee

For the bonuses, I request that any surf-timer server that plays this map to not allow teleporting to bonus with commands. There are entrances to both bonuses on the map.

More screenshots are available here


The zones (for surftimers) are as follows:

  • Stage 1 - stage1
  • Stage 2 - stage2
  • Stage 3 - stage3
  • Stage 4 - stage4
  • Stage 5 - stage5
  • Stage 6 - stage6
  • Stage 7 - stage7
  • Stage 8 - stage8
  • End of map - map_end
  • Bonus 1 Start - bonus1
  • Bonus 1 end - bonus1_end
  • Bonus 2 Start - bonus2
  • Bonus 2 End - bonus2_end

Xtra_Festive and I decided to make a quick map for april fool's day (originally released as surf_omnific2), with the one restriction that we can't test anything before release.

The map is 8 stages, tier 3-4, with telehops between the stages.

Surprisingly, each stage is doable despite never being tested prior to release.

The map was made in only 6 hours, but development will continue to turn it into an actual tested map.  This release is only to showcase what is possible without testing.
